{{h1}}Pull Request

- Review the current branch, commit history, and diff before opening the pull request
- Prepare a pull request title and body that accurately describe the change

{{h2}}Instructions

- Use {{#resource}}review/pr{{/resource}} to prepare the pull request message
- If `.github/pull_request_template.md` exists, use it as the starting structure for the pull request body
- Keep the body focused on user-visible or behavior-level changes rather than file-by-file detail
- Include relevant context, impact, and follow-up notes where appropriate
- Do not include "brag" information such as test related statistics or overzealous claims

{{h2}}Before Opening

- Confirm the current branch is ready to be proposed
- Push the branch if needed
- Open the pull request against the correct base branch using the prepared title and body
